A good earphone supposed to provide passive/innate noise reduction anyways since all ears are covered.. What this differentiate from other earphones is that this can be used wireless and wired and during wired or wireless, ANC can be turned on. SOme of the competitors like anker of this price range do not have ANC function when wired, do take note.

Performance: Good sound but a little lacking in bass.
Kind of an impulse buy to see if the positive reviews were true and turns out everyone's spitting facts. 

I'm not an audiophile by any definition of the term but headphones sounds really good though as I've mentioned above, it lacks in bass if you're into that sort of thing. I have not taken it out and about but Bluetooth connection seems solid as it is and the option to use a 3.5mm cable is also available. Material-wise it's not bad but also not impressive but still comfortable to wear AND for a guy with a big head like myself, it has decent enough clamping force it doesn't give me a headache. 

Downside if you have big ears like mine, the cups might not really fit your ears as well and you might have to origami your ears to fit it into cups. That being said I'm fine with it regardless and I intend to use it more. 

Overall if you don't want to spend too much on wireless headphones but still want quality,this is a great choice.

Performance: Great
Best Feature(s): Sound quality
Box had a few dents at the bottom so if you're particular about it, don't buy this as a gift. 

Pros:
- Great battery life. Wore them for 9hrs straight and the battery was at 90%. I used the headphones for about 3 to 4 days before I needed to charge it.
- Charging takes about 2 - 3hrs max for it to reach 100%.
- Bluetooth was very easy to connect and there's a instruction manual incase you need help.
- Two wires were provided in the box, one for charging the headphones and the other incase you prefer using wired headphones. Do take note that the headphones must be at least 20% or above (for wired) as there will be no sound if the headphones aren't charged.
- The headphones are lightweight, easy to keep & portable.
- Great sound quality and bass. If you like to listen to really loud music, I would recommend buying this. Even when the volume was high, my mum could not hear anything that I was listening to, so 10/10 for me.
- Incase you get tired of wearing the headphones, you can put it down & still hear the music/video quite well (increase the volume a lil bit) so the headphones can act as a "speaker" if you don't want to wear it anymore.
- The ANC (noise reduction) mode did block out some noise, although not all. But for the price paid, it's very worth the purchase. 

Cons:
- The headphones looked very bulky/big to me so if you're going for the aesthetic look, don't buy this. But if you're looking for good sound quality/bass & lightweight headphones, buy this.
- The top part of the headphones had a really small "cushion" so it was quite painful after a few hours.
- My ears started hurting after a while but after a week of using the headphones, it got better. 

Overall, for the price paid I would definitely recommend giving this a tryüëç
